}

\subtree{
\title{Implementation Workflow}
\p{To implement hooks in a plugin:}

\ol{
\li{Identify events to hook into (PreToolUse, Stop, SessionStart, etc.)}
\li{Decide between prompt-based (flexible) or command (deterministic) hooks}
\li{Write hook configuration in \code{\startverb hooks/hooks.json\stopverb}}
\li{For command hooks, create hook scripts}
\li{\startverb Use ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT} for all file references\stopverb}
\li{Validate configuration with \code{\startverb scripts/validate-hook-schema.sh hooks/hooks.json\stopverb}}
\li{Test hooks with \code{\startverb scripts/test-hook.sh\stopverb} before deployment}
\li{Test in Claude Code with \code{\startverb claude --debug\stopverb}}
\li{Document hooks in plugin README}
}

\p{Focus on prompt-based hooks for most use cases. Reserve command hooks for performance-critical or deterministic checks.}
}
}